    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-30T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-30T06:00:00-05:00" n="593"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/1034: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-30T20:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 30, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 1—4:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1246. In my interview with the Foreign Minister today, he prefaced our
                    conversation by expressing his apologies for his unavailable [<hi rend="italic"
                        >unavoidable?</hi>] delay in replying to previous representations respecting
                    Japanese interference with American rights and interests in China. He said that
                    he had started a full investigation of these cases but had been ill with
                    threatened pneumonia for some time. He, however, expected to make a full report
                    to me during the coming week.<note n="44" xml:id="d593fn44">For the Ambassador’s
                        memorandum of his conversation with the Japanese Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs, December 17, see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_895">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 895</ref>; for oral statements by the
                        Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs, December 17, see <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_895">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>., pp. 895</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_899">899</ref>.</note> I replied that I would
                    be interested in receiving his report but that concrete results would carry more
                    weight than explanations or assurances for the future.</p>
                <pb facs="0563" n="555" xml:id="pg_555"/>
                <p>Sent to the Department via Shanghai. Shanghai please repeat to Chungking and
                    Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
